Covariances were adopted from COMMARA-2.0 library in July 2011.    125 1451
These covariances were obtained at LANL by full scale R-matrix     125 1451
analysis of more than 5000 experimental data (chi-square/degree    125 1451
of freedom of 0.83). [1] The major channel in this case is elastic 125 1451
scattering, often labeled also as ''n-p'' scattering. Elastic      125 1451
scattering serves as neutron cross section standard from 1 keV to  125 1451
20 MeV, with cross sections well determined. Uncertainties for     125 1451
elastic scattering rise from values well below 1%, reach maximum   125 1451
at about 8 MeV, then gradually decrease with increasing energy.    125 1451
In addition to elastic scattering, covariances are supplied for    125 1451
radiative capture.                                                 125 1451
